The paper introduces a Python toolbox for active learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper discusses the implementation of active learning algorithms and their evaluation, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The toolbox also includes options for data processing, visualization, and multi-label data, which are relevant to computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and information retrieval (cs.IR).
